something simple, even if it's not perfect  

486
00:46:11,680 --> 00:46:17,000
and your composite would be more perfect. If 
people understand it, if they have an intuition  

487
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:22,480
around it, if it's something that people can talk 
about across the company, it's going to be a much  

488
00:46:22,480 --> 00:46:29,880
better metric in terms of driving real outcomes 
than your made up composite score that nobody  

489
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:35,400
understands. So I think keeping things simple is 
also really important. And then I think the last  

